### Delivery information

Some VistaPrint products and destinations are not available in all shipping speeds. Most, but not all, of these are listed right here.

- __Clothing & bags:__ 10+ business days
- __Promotional products:__ 10+ business days
- __Photobooks__:  6 or 8 business days
- __Sample kits:__ 14 business days
- __Checks:__ 6 or 8 business days
  __Please note:__ For security purposes, checks can only be shipped to the address printed on the check – and they cannot be sent to P.O. boxes

If your order includes products with different shipping speeds, it can be split into separate packages. This avoids delaying products that you can receive sooner.

You'll have a choice of shipping speeds, depending on which products are in your cart. For example, if some of your items are available for Express shipping, you will be able to choose this option. You only need to select and pay for one speed.

Before you make the payment, we’ll show you how your order will be split and the estimated date that each product will be delivered to you. This means you’ll know prior to purchase which products in your cart may arrive later than your chosen delivery speed.

# Responsibly sourced paper products

The Forest Stewardship Council® helps maintain and protect forests - and their inhabitants - for future generations. 95% of the paper we print on is FSC® certified.

FSC certification ensures that healthy forests are maintained, and the rights of forestry workers and forest dwellers are protected.

This means we can serve small businesses around the world while acting to reduce our impact on the environment.

Learn more about our [FSC® certification](https://sustainability.vistaprint.com/responsible-forestry/) and our [commitment to sustainability](https://sustainability.vistaprint.com/).

answer.answer: All the business cards we produce for North American and European markets are FSC-certified, except ColorFill, Colored Paper and Ultra Thick paper stocks.

question.question: Could I use the FSC logo on my marketing materials?

answer.answer:
VistaPrint has earned the right to use the FSC and Rainforest Alliance logos on our marketing materials and packaging, but we are also responsible for ensuring that they are used legitimately and in accordance with our agreements with those organizations.

Due to the many different ways customers might wish to use these logos in their designs, it is unfortunately not permitted to customize our products with these logos at this time.

question.question: What FSC-certified products do you sell?

answer.answer:
It is highly likely that any paper-based products that you order from VistaPrint are printed on paper that has been confirmed as FSC certified up to our supplier’s facilities.

We intend to continue to expand our chain of custody processes in the coming months so that we can expand our FSC product offering, so stay tuned for updates.

description.description:
- 12 size options 
- Glossy & matte finish options
- Resealable zip & hang-hole options
- Self-standing display
- Full-color printing on the front, back & bottom 

__Seal, stand up & stand out __

Looking for a way to present your goods in an eye-catching way? Whether you sell pet food, tea leaves or anything in between, our flexible stand-up pouch bags will seal your products up tight and protect them from the outside world. With your custom design on them, these self-standing pouches will help your product stand out on the counter and table displays. 

__Options to set your packaging apart __

Choose from a variety of sizes to find the one that suits your dry, wet, powdered or confectionery packaging needs. Pick a matte or glossy finish to help your pouch bags stand out. Then consider adding a premium feature – a resealable zip to extend the life of your product or a hang hole so that it can be hung on display. 

__Easy design experience __

When you're ready to start designing your pouch bags, you have options: Upload your own design, explore our customizable templates or let one of our pros create a one-of-a-kind design for you. You'll be able to review your design in 3D to make sure it's just right before we take care of the rest. Your stand-up pouches will arrive printed and opened at the top. When you fill your pouch and heat-seal to close, your product will be ready to impress.

question.question: Will my flex pouches arrive sealed?

answer.answer: No. All our flat pouches are printed and shipped opened at the top. After filling, we highly recommend using a heat sealer on the top to seal securely – even if you order pouches with a zip. This protects contents from being exposed to the elements or damaged in transit.

question.question: What can I pack inside my stand-up pouches?

answer.answer:
Flexible packaging is versatile, great for:

- Tea.
- Health & beauty: scrubs, shampoo, lotions, liquid soap and other cosmetics.
- Supplements: vitamins, oil capsules, protein powder and more.
- Food & drink: fruits, nuts, cereals, dairy, herbs, spices, cured meat, smoothies, juices and even frozen food.
- Pet food: dry and wet food.

question.question: Are these custom pouches suitable for food packaging?

answer.answer: Yes, our pouches are FDA approved for direct food contact. It's safe to microwave them. You can put them in a freezer up to 5 degrees Fahrenheit (not suitable for deep freezing). Plus, they're leak proof for liquids.

question.question: Does your pouch packaging help extend the life of products?

answer.answer: Yes. The film material blocks moisture and oxygen, which helps keep the product fresh.

question.question: How can I decide if I need a resealable zip?

answer.answer:
If your customer is likely to discard the pouch immediately after your product has been removed, then you don't need a zipper. 

If your product is designed for long-term use, we recommend adding a zipper to make it easy for customers to open and close the pouch. 

If you choose to add a zipper, a single-track zip will be added 1.25" to 1.5" from the top edge of the pouch, depending on pouch size. To see exact placement by size, you can download a template of your desired size from the "Specs & Templates" section of this page.

question.question: Are the hanging hole options available on all stand-up pouch sizes?

answer.answer: The Euro hole option is not available on our smallest size pouch (3.25" x 4.75"), but we do offer a round hole option for that size.

question.question: What are the sizes of hanging hole punches?

answer.answer:
The round hole is 0.31" (8 mm) in diameter. 
The Euro hole is 0.39" (10 mm) high and 0.98" (25 mm) long.

question.question: Can I print on all sides of my pouch packaging?

answer.answer: Yes, you can print on the front, the back and even the bottom of the pouch. The bottom is often used to put bar codes and non-essential information. Keep in mind that there is a fold line and crease in the center of the bottom section.

question.question: What is the minimal quantity I can order?

answer.answer: The minimum quantity order is 100 stand-up pouches.
